l context to a wide variety of American practices and beliefs and, in doing so, provide a new framework for understanding cultural life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aAmerican Studies. 4aU.S. History.1 aHalttunen, Karen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPerry, Lewis, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172549440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501725494423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501725494/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles